body: @avinashpaliwal  hello avinash how do i run the train.ipynb in conda environment...i know for python we use python filename.py and then enter ,,,so it runs

Hi @eng100200 if you have downloaded the [anaconda UI application](https://docs.anaconda.com/anaconda/navigator/), you can launch the [JupyterLab](https://medium.com/@brianray_7981/jupyterlab-first-impressions-e6d70d8a175d) or [Notebook](https://jupyter-notebook-beginner-guide.readthedocs.io/en/latest/execute.html)
or run the command from project directory:
```bash
jupyter notebook
```
or
```bash
jupyter lab
```
Then you can open the `train.ipynb` file in jupyter.

I am also going to commit `train.py`, so that you can train it directly from terminal.

Thanks Avinash Paliwal, and happy new year. 
However, I mean Avinash Paliwal that i still want to use python command prompt and want to run ipynb file. then how can i do it?
@eng100200  I have added the [train.py](https://github.com/avinashpaliwal/Super-SloMo/blob/master/train.py) script. You can now train from terminal.
